        "app_name": "Ambulate using Transfer Belt Simulator",
        "release_date": "1980-01-01T00:00:00.000Z",
        "description": "In this VR simulation, learners will master the process of assisting patients to ambulate using a transfer belt. The tutorial covers preparation, communication, application of the transfer belt, and the ambulation process itself. By the end of this tutorial, participants will be able to: \n- Remember the necessary steps and safety protocols for using a transfer belt. \n- Understand the importance of proper transfer techniques in patient safety. \n- Apply the correct method to secure the transfer belt and assist patients in ambulation. \n- Analyze the patient's condition and environment to adjust the approach as needed. \n- Evaluate their technique to ensure it adheres to best practices and safety standards. \n- Create a safe and supportive environment for patients during ambulation using a transfer belt. \n\nThis comprehensive approach ensures CNAs are well-prepared to assist patients with proper care efficiently and compassionately in real-world clinical settings. ",
